I tend to do this:<br>
<br>
/w 62 65 cleric<br>
/t cleric I'm donating 100pp for virtue please<br>
<br>
If I get a &quot;no,&quot; I reply &quot;k thx&quot; and move on. <br>
If I get a &quot;yes,&quot; i ask where they are so they don't have to move<br>
If I get no response, I move on.<br>
<br>
I don't think I'm rude about it though, and I've never received any tells indicating that I was rude or that they placed me on /ignore.<br>
<br>
If I get no response from /tells then I will /ooc and create a line of zone spam in order to see if any /roleplay clerics wish to help me.  Line is almost always the same.<br>
<br>
/shout Donating 100pp for Virtue Please<br>
<br>
I always try to say please in my request.  I think being polite about a request does make a difference as to whether I get a response or not.<br>
<br>
But, reading above msg's, maybe I am being a selfsih ignorant noob.<br>
