haha, that reminds me of what happened 3 nights ago.<br>
<br>
I was sitting in Nexus, and someone walks up and sends me a /hail.  Like an idiot, I /hail back because curiosity *always* gets the better of me.  Sure enough, he was begging for something to help him get a new BP.<br>
<br>
So I say, &quot;sure, come with me,&quot; and truck off to Shadowhaven.  When we get there, I go to the bank, and he follows me (I have to make it look like I'm getting something).  Back outside the bank (i'm grouped with him at this time), I tell him to make it official, he needs to target me and type in /d.<br>
<br>
About five seconds go by, and then says &quot;I'm not a noob, there's no way I'm going to duel you.&quot;  I tell him if he's not a noob then why is he begging.....his response is.....<br>
Because it's fun.  He degroups and runs off<br>
<br>
I wasn't going to post it at all because it was in fact a failed beggar hunt.  Hopefully the next one will be more succesfull, and I'll have some fun reading to post for you all.<br>
<br>
